 make them quad.  Are they actually quadding against the kind of mobs you'd throw them at for 140's? I doubt it.  Maybe against a weak glass-jawed wizard, but not against mobs of their ilk and greater.<br>
<br>
That... and AQ (or shissar even) + berserker spirit + feedback (or whatever the DS i'm thinking of is called) = one scary ass pet.<br>
<br>
Of course, Dire Charm isn't quite as bad as some of the non-AA charm sprees I've seen... I recall my friend Mylowe going from 53-56 in a couple days, charm kiting with Yvolcarn in Cobalt Scar.  If he wanted it dead; it was dead in 10 seconds.  Including Azureake, who barely put a dent in Yvolcarn.  Otters are a different story though... seems half attack Yvolcarn and the other half beeline for the chanter... ug.<br>
<br>
Kinda entertaining watching people bitch about the trains and then boggle when they heard someone was charm kiting him. =)<br>
<br>
